### Step 1 — Register Enterprise App + Configure SAML

Run the setup script to create the Azure AD Enterprise Application, configure SAML 2.0 SSO, generate a signing cert, and assign the lab group.

```powershell
.\scripts\powershell\01-AzureAD-SSO-Setup.ps1 `
    -TenantId        "your-tenant-id" `
    -AppDisplayName  "IAM-SSO-MFA-Lab" `
    -AssignmentGroup "SSO-Lab-Users" `
    -ReplyUrl        "https://sp.lab.local/simplesaml/module.php/saml/sp/saml2-acs.php/lab-sp" `
    -EntityId        "https://sp.lab.local"
```

**What the script does:**

- Registers Application + Service Principal in Entra ID
- Sets `PreferredSingleSignOnMode = "saml"`
- Generates 3-year RSA token signing certificate
- Assigns the `SSO-Lab-Users` security group
- Outputs federation metadata (SSO URL, Entity ID, cert thumbprint)

