### Step 2 — Create Conditional Access + MFA Policies

Creates three CA policies targeting the lab app:

|Policy                    |Scope                      |Grant Control         |
|--------------------------|---------------------------|----------------------|
|`[LAB] Require MFA`       |All users, all client apps |Require MFA           |
|`[LAB] Block Legacy Auth` |All users, legacy protocols|Block                 |
|`[LAB] Risk-Based Step-Up`|Sign-in risk: Medium/High  |MFA + Compliant device|

```powershell
# Run Report-Only first to validate impact before enforcing
.\scripts\powershell\02-MFA-ConditionalAccess.ps1 `
    -TenantId    "your-tenant-id" `
    -TargetAppId "your-app-client-id"

# Add -EnablePolicies to enforce (removes report-only mode)
.\scripts\powershell\02-MFA-ConditionalAccess.ps1 `
    -TenantId    "your-tenant-id" `
    -TargetAppId "your-app-client-id" `
    -EnablePolicies
```

>  **Always validate with Entra ID → Security → Conditional Access → What If before enabling.**

**Conditional Access policy blade — all 3 policies enabled:**

