## 🔧 Okta as IdP (Alternative Path)

The `configs/okta/` directory has API payloads for Okta instead of Azure AD:

```bash
# Register SAML app
curl -s -X POST "https://{yourOktaDomain}/api/v1/apps" \
  -H "Authorization: SSWS ${OKTA_API_TOKEN}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d @configs/okta/okta-saml-app.json

# Apply MFA enrollment policy
curl -s -X POST "https://{yourOktaDomain}/api/v1/policies" \
  -H "Authorization: SSWS ${OKTA_API_TOKEN}" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d @configs/okta/okta-mfa-policy.json
```

